            <h2><a name="Summary"></a>Summary</h2>

<p>This issue involves implementing error handling tests for validation errors, server errors, and error recovery in the application.</p>

<h2><a name="Context"></a>Context</h2>

<p>The goal is to ensure that users receive clear feedback when errors occur. This includes validation errors for input, server errors, and the ability to recover from these errors.</p>

<h2><a name="Acceptancecriteria"></a>Acceptance criteria</h2>

<h3><a name="Task5.1%3ATestvalidationerrors"></a>Task 5.1: Test validation errors</h3>

<ul>
	<li>All validation error tests implemented</li>
	<li>Error messages are clear and specific</li>
	<li>Input fields highlighted appropriately</li>
</ul>


<h3><a name="Task5.2%3ATestservererrors"></a>Task 5.2: Test server errors</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Server error scenarios tested</li>
	<li>User-friendly error messages shown</li>
	<li>No silent failures</li>
</ul>


<h3><a name="Task5.3%3ATesterrorrecovery"></a>Task 5.3: Test error recovery</h3>

<ul>
	<li>User can correct errors and retry</li>
	<li>Error state cleanup working</li>
	<li>No lingering error messages</li>
</ul>


<h2><a name="Otherinformation"></a>Other information</h2>

<h3><a name="TaskEstimates"></a>Task Estimates</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Task 5.1: 3 hours</li>
	<li>Task 5.2: 2 hours</li>
	<li>Task 5.3: 2 hours</li>
</ul>


<h3><a name="TeststoImplement"></a>Tests to Implement</h3>

<ul>
	<li><tt>test_user_sees_clear_error_for_invalid_nfft</tt> - NFFT not power of 2</li>
	<li><tt>test_user_sees_error_for_frequency_exceeds_limit</tt> - Frequency &gt; 1000 Hz</li>
	<li><tt>test_user_sees_error_for_invalid_channels</tt> - Invalid channel range</li>
	<li><tt>test_user_sees_error_when_server_unavailable</tt> - Server down scenario</li>
	<li><tt>test_user_sees_error_for_timeout</tt> - Request timeout scenario</li>
</ul>


<h3><a name="ErrorRecoveryTests"></a>Error Recovery Tests</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Verify user can correct invalid input</li>
	<li>Verify retry button functionality</li>
	<li>Verify error state is properly cleared</li>
</ul>

